This paper deals with predicting software growth and evaluating prediction approaches in an industrial setting, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning (cs.LG) and statistical approaches (cs.PL) for prediction. Additionally, the paper discusses eliciting expectations from practitioners (cs.AI) and measuring software size through mining revision history (cs.SD).
